The paper focuses on imitation learning for robot policies, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The approach combines natural language, vision, and motion information, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of vision also suggests a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of natural language suggests a potential focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
